<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12045g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12045g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12045g"> 45(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cut away gilt capitals</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le hasard, dit M. de Gerville, me conduisit dans un grenier plac&eacute; au-dessus de la biblioth&egrave;que o&ugrave; j&apos;aper&ccedil;us de sales et poudreux in-folios, jet&eacute;s &agrave; l&apos;aventure. Les premiers que j&apos;ouvris &eacute;taient d&apos;anciens manuscrits sur v&eacute;lin, d&apos;une &eacute;criture soign&eacute;e et passablement conserv&eacute;e; quelques-uns avaient des initiales dor&eacute;es et enlumin&eacute;es; dans quelques autres, cette dorure avait excit&eacute; la cupidit&eacute; des enfants et des oisifs; elle avait &eacute;t&eacute; coup&eacute;e &agrave; l&apos;aide de ciseaux. L&apos;&eacute;criture ordinaire n&apos;avait tent&eacute; personne et n&apos;avait essuy&eacute; d&apos;autres injures que celles du temps. Nous pass&acirc;mes plusieurs heures &agrave; les appareiller et &agrave; en faire l&apos;inventaire et nous y retrouv&acirc;mes le pr&eacute;cieux Cartulaire dont nous d&eacute;plorions la perte. <br>[Luck, M. de Gerville tells us, led me into an attic above the library where I saw dirty and dusty in-folios thrown at hazard. The first I opened turned out to be ancient manuscripts on vellum, of a careful writing and more or less well conserved; some of them had gold and illuminated initials; in a few others <mark>this gold had aroused the greed of the idle or of children: it had been cut out by means of a pair of scissors</mark>. The ordinary writing had tempted nobody and it had suffered no other wounds than those of time. We passed <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 25</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
